gasiyqaAtN 
Intensely red; 
[applied to she-camels;] thus expl. by Skr as occurring in a verse of Sakhr [?] El-Hudhalee. (TA.)

1. gasaA All-ayolu, (Ṣ, Ḳ,) aor. yagosuw, (Ṣ,) inf. n. gusuw-N; (Ṣ, Ḳ; accord. to some copies of the Ḳ gasowN;) and gasaI, aor. yagosiI; (IJ, TA;) and gasiIa, aor. yagosaI, (Ṣ, Ḳ, TA,) inf. n. gasFA; of which last form, gaXiIa is a dial. var.; (TA;) The night was, or became, dark; 
as also AgsI↓. (Ṣ, Ḳ.) 
[See also EasaA.]

hom.sense:
One says of the night, yagoXaI biZulomatihi kul-a maA bayona Als-amaMCi waAlOaroDi [It covers, or conceals, with its darkness, everything that is between the heaven and the earth]. (Jel in xcii. 1.) 
And [hence it is said that] gaXiIa All-ayolu means The night was, or became, dark; 
as also AgXI↓. (Mṣb, TA.)

